<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 05 at 12:36PM CDT  by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
McCurtain County through 115 PM CDT...
At 1235 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles southwest of Octavia, or 33 miles southeast of Clayton, moving
northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Plunketville, Watson, Bethel, Mount Herman, Smithville and Sherwood.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
